            "text": "{\"correctness\":{\"rating\":\"partial\",\"justification\":\"Most positions are correctly stated. However, the answer lists 'Vice-Director of the Institute of Informatics at UFRGS: 2011 - 2016' but the curriculum shows two separate vice-director periods (12/2011-12/2015 and 12/2015-10/2016), which is acceptable as a combined range. The 'Coordinator of the Steering Committee of the Graduate Program' (President of the Forum of Coordinators) is described somewhat inaccurately - the curriculum says 'Presidente do Forum de Coordenadores de Pós-Graduação da UFRGS' (04/1999-05/2000), not coordinator of the steering committee of the graduate program. The SBC Director role is listed but is not strictly an academic administrative position (course coordinator, department chair, academic unit director, or graduate program coordinator) as asked. Overall mostly correct with minor inaccuracies.\"},\"completeness\":{\"rating\":\"meets\",\"justification\":\"The answer covers all major administrative positions mentioned in the curriculum context relevant to the question: director and vice-director of the institute, department head, specialization course coordinator, graduate program coordinator and vice-coordinator (both periods), and the forum presidency. The SBC and CEGRAPI roles are included as additional context. No significant omissions relative to what the curriculum provides.\"}}",
